Patch summary:
Apply the framework and SystemUI desktop contract. This patch gathers the
platform-level behavior that makes the guest act like a desktop VM: desktop-mode
defaults, freeform/window behavior, Quick Settings cleanup, display power
behavior, storage reporting, status bar/shade adjustments, and other VM-facing
framework defaults.

Most of the changes are about replacing phone assumptions with desktop ones.
The guest has no useful battery saver, flashlight, wallet, auto-rotate, or
screen-sleep affordance, and its display/window model is host-driven. Keeping
that policy in the framework layer gives Launcher and the product overlays a
stable desktop contract to build on.

